We can use this proportion:

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&\triangle WXY
\\
{\text{adjacent to } \atop 70\degree\text{ angle}}
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\maroonD{\dfrac{WY}{3.4}}=\blueE{\dfrac{WX}{10}}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&\scriptsize\text{hypotenuse}
\\
&\text{triangle }\boxed{1}
\end{array}$



[[☃ image 1]]

Now we can rewrite the equation to show the ratios of the side lengths *within* each triangle.

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&{\text{adjacent to } \atop 70\degree\text{ angle}}
\\
\scriptsize\triangle WXY
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\dfrac{WY}{WX}=\dfrac{3.4}{10}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&\scriptsize\text{triangle }\boxed{1}
\\
&\scriptsize\text{hypotenuse}
\end{array}$

